label.value: HMGCR wt Allele

value.value: Human HMGCR wild-type allele is located within 5q13.3-q14 and is approximately 25 kb in length. This allele, which encodes 3-hydroxy-3-methylglutaryl-coenzyme A reductase protein, plays a role in the regulation of cholesterol biosynthesis.

label.value: Ceruminous Adenoma

value.value: A benign epithelial neoplasm derived from ceruminous glands in the external auditory canal. It presents as a grey mass covered by skin. It is characterized by a proliferation of glands composed of cells with abundant eosinophilic and granular cytoplasm.

label.value: Single Cell Necrosis

value.value: A morphologic finding indicating the presence of individual necrotic cells surrounded by viable cells in a tissue sample.

label.value: Cytoplasmic Membrane-Bound Granules Present
Recombinant Bispecific Single-Chain Antibody rM28

value.value: A recombinant, bispecific, single-chain antibody directed against both the T-cell surface-associated costimulatory molecule CD28 and a melanoma-associated proteoglycan (MAPG) with potential antitumor activity. By targeting both CD28 and MAPG, recombinant bispecific single-chain antibody rM28 enhances cytotoxic T-cell recognition of melanoma cells, which may result in immune effector cell-mediated tumor cell death and a decrease in distant metastases. This agent appears to have a long serum half-life secondary to the formation of dimers. When activated, CD28 facilitates interactions between T-cells and other immune effector cells resulting in cytotoxic T-lymphocyte responses; MAPG is a surface antigen expressed on the majority of melanomas, including primary cutaneous, ocular, and metastatic melanomas.

label.value: Iron Sucrose Injection

value.value: A sterile aqueous complex of polynuclear iron (III)-hydroxide in sucrose for intravenous use. Following intravenous administration, iron sucrose is dissociated by the reticuloendothelial system into iron and sucrose; the sucrose component is eliminated mainly by urinary excretion. Iron sucrose can be administered with or without erythropoietin to raise hemoglobin levels and may be used in cases of oral iron therapy intolerance or ineffectiveness. Hypersensitivity reactions are less common with iron sucrose compared to other parenteral iron products, such as iron dextran.

label.value: Cloth Dosage Form

value.value: A solid composed active and/or inert ingredient(s) in a woven absorbent material.

label.value: Ovarian Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v6

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system. TNM clinical findings are based on information obtained prior to the first definitive treatment through physical examination, diagnostic imaging, biopsy or laboratory testing.

label.value: Ovarian Cancer TNM Finding v6

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system.

label.value: Ovarian Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system.

label.value: Ovarian Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases. TNM pathologic distant metastasis findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

label.value: Middle Ear Carcinoma

value.value: A carcinoma that arises from the middle ear.  This category includes adenocarcinoma and squamous cell carcinoma.

label.value: Ovarian Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor. TNM pathologic primary tumor findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

label.value: Concentrated Dosage Form

value.value: A solution or suspension composed of active and/or inert ingredient(s) with increased strength in a reduced volume, which is usually diluted prior to administration.

label.value: Ovarian Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Ovarian Cancer pM0 TNM Finding

value.value: Ovarian cancer with no evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer pMX TNM Finding v6

value.value: Ovarian cancer in which distant metastasis cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer pM1 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Ovarian cancer with distant metastasis, excluding peritoneal metastasis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Augmented Cream Dosage Form

value.value: A cream that is modified to enhance the release of active and/or inert ingredient(s).

label.value: Ovarian Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Ovarian cancer without involvement of regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Ovarian cancer with metastasis to one or more regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Leukotriene B4

value.value: A leukotriene synthesized from leukotriene A4 by leukotriene A-4 hydrolase in monocytes, lymphocytes, neutrophils, reticulocytes, platelets and fibroblasts. Leukotriene B4 modulates inflammation by promoting neutrophil activation and inducing adhesion, activation, and transendothelial migration of leukocytes.

label.value: Lacrimal Gland Malignant Mixed Tumor
Ovarian Cancer pNX TNM Finding v6

value.value: Ovarian cancer in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer pTX TNM Finding v6

value.value: Ovarian cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Ovarian cancer with no evidence of a primary tumor. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Ovarian cancer with tumor confined to one or both ovaries. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer pT1a TNM Finding v6

value.value: Ovarian cancer with tumor in one ovary with capsule intact, no tumor on ovarian surface and no malignant cells in either ascites or peritoneal washings. The presence of ascites does not affect staging unless malignant cells are present. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer pT1b TNM Finding v6

value.value: Ovarian cancer with tumor in both ovaries with capsule intact, no tumor on ovarian surface and no malignant cells in either ascites or peritoneal washings. The presence of ascites does not affect staging unless malignant cells are present. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer pT1c TNM Finding v6

value.value: Ovarian cancer involving one or both ovaries with either a ruptured capsule, or tumor on the ovarian surface, or presence of malignant cells in either ascites or peritoneal washings. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Ovarian cancer involving one or both ovaries with pelvic extension and/or implants. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer pT2a TNM Finding v6

value.value: Ovarian cancer involving one or both ovaries with extension or implants on uterus and/or fallopian tubes and without malignant cells in ascites or peritoneal washings. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Lacrimal Gland Mucoepidermoid Carcinoma

value.value: An extremely rare carcinoma that arises from the lacrimal gland.  It is characterized by the presence of infiltrating nests of epidermoid cells and mucus producing cells.

label.value: Ovarian Cancer pT2b TNM Finding v6

value.value: Ovarian cancer involving one or both ovaries with extension or implants on pelvic tissues other than the uterus or fallopian tubes, and without malignant cells in ascites or peritoneal washings. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer pT2c TNM Finding v6

value.value: Ovarian cancer involving one or both ovaries with extension or implants on the uterus and/or fallopian tubes, or other pelvic tissues, with malignant cells in either ascites or peritoneal washings. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v6

value.value: Ovarian cancer involving one or both ovaries with microscopic or macroscopic peritoneal metastasis beyond the pelvis. (from ACJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer pT3a TNM Finding v6

value.value: Ovarian cancer involving one or both ovaries with microscopically confirmed peritoneal metastasis beyond the pelvis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer pT3b TNM Finding v6

value.value: Ovarian cancer involving one or both ovaries with macroscopic peritoneal metastasis beyond the pelvis, with tumor size of 2 cm or less in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Ovarian Cancer pT3c TNM Finding v6

value.value: Ovarian cancer involving one or both ovaries with macroscopic peritoneal metastasis beyond the pelvis, with tumor size of more than 2 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Bone Conduction Assessment

value.value: A test of the transmission of sound to the inner ear through the bones of the skull. This testing can measure functionality of the inner ear independent of the functionality of the outer and middle ears.

label.value: Static Admittance

value.value: The maximum compliance (mobility) of the middle ear system (i.e., the greatest amount of acoustic energy absorbed by the middle ear system (the vertical peak of the tympanogram tracing).
